FBIS4-63358 "drsov099_a_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Fleet Begins Scheduled Exercises Fleet Begins Scheduled Exercises LD2005210794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1830 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005210794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [From the "Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense Ministry] [Text] More than 20 combat ships, support vessels, and submarines have left the main base of the Black Sea Fleet. Until 22 May, the Black Sea Fleet is holding the scheduled exercises of the fleet's various forces, including firing practice and the targeting and elimination submarines. The exercises are kind summation of the results of a training period, preparations for the summer campaign, and at the same time, a competition to win the navy prizes.
